Name: The Elevator Game with Catgirls
About the game: The Elevator Game with Catgirls is a horror visual novel with point-and-click elements, inspired by the Korean urban legend, Elevator to Another World . - Catgirls! - An eerie atmospheric setting - Short sessions with multiple endings (11 main + 4 secret ones) - Point-and-click elements (explore and find clues!) - Timed choices (optional) - Over 500 backgrounds - Full voice-over - Did we mention catgirls? :) The Elevator Game is a ritual that is said to give the player access to another world by following a strict set of rules. Motivated by a bet made with her classmate, Asahi's girlfriend Kirin decides to give the game a try. As Asahi waits outside of the building that Kirin chose to perform the ritual in, she starts to experience some confusing and unexplainable things... Kirin fails to return that day, or the day after. Feeling somehow guilty as though Kirin's disappearance might be her fault, Asahi determines to try and find her missing girlfriend... by playing the Elevator Game herself. Will your choices help find her? This game contains content that may not be appropriate for all ages. Some situations depicted might be disturbing or triggering. Player discretion is advised. Nayru - Story & Script / Game Design / Coding KleeBentz - Art / Character Design / 3D Modeling Xolf - Co-writing / Coding Assistance Music composed by OddTillTheEnd
